After talking with @kantai, we want to support constructions like this:
```
    let contract_defining_trait = 
        "(define-trait trait-1 (
            (get-1 (uint) (response uint uint))))";
    let dispatching_contract =
        "(use-trait trait-1 .defun.trait-1)
        (define-public (wrapped-get-1 (contract <trait-1>)) 
            (contract-call? contract get-1 u0))";
    let impl_contract = 
        "(impl-trait .defun.trait-1)
        (define-public (get-1 (x uint)) (ok u1))";
    let caller_contract =
        "(define-public (foo-bar)
           (contract-call? .dispatch wrapped-get-1 .implem))"; 
```
meaning we also want to be able to pass literals (`.implem`) in a cascade of `contract-call`.
As such, we need to statically infer, using the context, that `.implem` is implementing a given trait (knowing that .implem could be implementing multiple traits)

